1
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:17,017
The smell of a human house

2
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:23,189
Narrow, cramped,

3
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:26,693
and...

4
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,244
What's the meaning of this

5
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:39,456
D, don't you dare move

6
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,417
I saw everything you did yesterday

7
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:45,587
Red eyes and fangs

8
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:47,922
Are you a vampire?

9
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:52,010
I get the rope,

10
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:52,969
but seriously,

11
00:00:52,969 --> 00:00:55,513
what's with the garlic and the cross?

12
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:58,224
I've seen it in movies

13
00:00:58,224 --> 00:01:01,227
They said vampires are weak
against garlic and crosses

14
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:03,271
Shoo

15
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:05,315
You are afraid of it, huh?

16
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:06,691
Don't move

17
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:09,444
Darn humans

18
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:10,904
That's all a myth

19
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,615
The vampires of the 21st century have evolved

20
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,617
Garlic? It just smells

21
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:17,577
Cross?

22
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,204
I'm also a Christian

23
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:27,128
Then, what about sunlight?

24
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:28,922
I can just put on sunscreen

25
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:43,853
You really look like you're powerless

26
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,606
It's because of your blood

27
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:48,358
Your blood

28
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:52,028
destroyed something inside me

29
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,727
I don't know what's going on

30
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:27,897
But tying someone up

31
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,400
isn't humane

32
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,780
I'm not human, though

33
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:37,991
But thanks

34
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,368
I never thought I'd receive help from a human

35
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:43,204
By the way,

36
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,623
Why are you so weak?

37
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:49,961
Shouldn't eating human blood
make you stronger or something?

38
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:54,465
And I'm supposed to be sick,
but why am I healthier?

39
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:56,885
Your blood

40
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:59,429
isn't just regular human blood

41
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:02,974
And that sweet scent

42
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:06,644
I shouldn't have drunk your blood

43
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,607
I'm not sure what happened,

44
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:12,901
But ever since I drank your blood,

45
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:14,485
My body got weaker,

46
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:16,905
and I can't use my powers

47
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,783
My fangs aren't even growing

48
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:24,954
Speaking of which,

49
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:27,749
can I suck your blood again?

50
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:30,960
That's absolutely not allowed

51
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:34,672
Okay, human

52
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:35,798
Then give me some water

53
00:03:36,966 --> 00:03:38,593
Okay

54
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,224
If I can't get your blood, can I get this?

55
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:01,991
W, what was that?

56
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:07,247
I thought I could suck your blood
from your lips, but I can't

57
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:08,539
What?

58
00:04:08,539 --> 00:04:10,208
Are you insane?

59
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:14,879
Oh, my part-time job

60
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:21,010
Hey, vampire

61
00:04:21,844 --> 00:04:24,097
I won't report you to the police

62
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,224
So go back to your world

63
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:30,103
If you're still here
after I'm back from work,

64
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:32,605
I'll report you for trespassing

65
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:34,232
Report?

66
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:36,609
You think people can arrest me,

67
00:04:36,609 --> 00:04:39,279
Lucifer, the crown prince
of the royal vampires?

68
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:41,322
What are you talking about?

69
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:43,908
Whether you're a crown prince or not,

70
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:46,661
just go back to your world

71
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:49,372
I'm sure you guys also have a hospital

72
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,208
Go there and get treated quickly

73
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:54,127
And I'm actually
really late for work

74
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:19,986
No way

75
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:22,405
Is it because I got too far?

76
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:41,632
Certainly

77
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:46,596
We can't be too far from each other

78
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,100
What do you mean?

79
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:54,604
Our bloods are intertwined,

80
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:56,981
in a state of interdependence

81
00:05:56,981 --> 00:06:00,193
If either of us gets too far away,
our body systems will collapse

82
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,154
So?

83
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:08,117
Does that mean we must
always stick together?

84
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:09,869
Yes

85
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:13,247
Simply put, it's a shared body plan

86
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:16,793
You're my medicine, and I'm your vaccine

87
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:20,797
Why am I involved in this?

88
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:22,632
Me too

89
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:25,218
It's the first time I've almost died
after drinking human blood

90
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:31,557
Okay

91
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:36,521
So,

92
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,148
- we have to be together
- We have to be together

93
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:45,196
Just until we find a solution

94
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:46,739
That's it

95
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:48,699
Yes

96
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:51,119
Just until we find a solution

97
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:55,248
But it seems like it'd take a while

98
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,292
Let's stay

99
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,963
at least 3m from each other

100
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:07,009
You're a very unique human

101
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:10,263
You're a very unique vampire, too

102
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,520
Let's leave now

103
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:32,910
Hurry up

104
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:43,004
Didn't know I was this handsome

105
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:52,638
I told you not to act weird

106
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:54,432
Just hurry

107
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:03,232
Hey, Minu

108
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:04,484
Hello, sir

109
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:07,695
You came a little early today?

110
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:08,696
Yes

111
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,785
Is that your friend?

112
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:17,914
Ah

113
00:08:18,581 --> 00:08:19,665
He is

114
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:21,542
uh...

115
00:08:21,542 --> 00:08:23,753
My cousin

116
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:26,923
He came up from the country,
and he's helping me work today

117
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:29,091
Oh, that's good

118
00:08:29,091 --> 00:08:31,344
We've been really short-staffed lately

119
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:34,931
I'd be grateful to get some help for a day

120
00:08:35,973 --> 00:08:37,475
He's your cousin?

121
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,893
What's his name?

122
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,311
I am vampire...

123
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,771
Jun, it's Jun

124
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:43,314
His name is Jun

125
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,775
Why are you changing my name?

126
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:46,442
I am Luci...

127
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:49,570
No, this is the human world,
and you're currently in disguise

128
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:52,281
Your real name is too odd and demonic

129
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:53,783
So you're Jun, okay?

130
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:54,784
You get it?

131
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:59,497
Jun is beneath my dignity

132
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,126
Jun

133
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:06,337
Nice to meet you

134
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:09,173
You can ask Minu for help
and learn the ropes

135
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:12,843
I will

136
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:20,101
Your cousin seems to be a bit candid

137
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,227
As are you

138
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:22,728
Sir,

139
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,898
My cousin has lived abroad for a while

140
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:27,233
Please go easy on him

141
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,859
I'm very sorry

142
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:31,320
Okay

143
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,115
Please take care of yourself

144
00:09:38,703 --> 00:09:41,914
Please don't cause any trouble
and just be quiet, okay?

145
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,917
But that would be boring

146
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:47,962
I'll see how you do

147
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:14,614
Do you use this machine
to extract blood from weak humans?

148
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:16,991
No

149
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:20,077
It's just for making coffee, not blood

150
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:32,840
Okay, here's how you do it

151
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,009
And you politely offer it to the customer

152
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:36,969
and say, "Thank you"

153
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:37,928
Try it

154
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,224
Drink this

155
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:43,517
No

156
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:46,020
Offer it politely

157
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:47,980
And say, "Thank you"

158
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:51,525
How can a royalty bow to humans?

159
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:56,530
We're in Korea right now, not your world

160
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,699
If you don't you'll be kicked out

161
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:00,660
Then, we're both in big trouble

162
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,537
Okay, I understand

163
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:05,998
Th...

164
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:07,958
Th, thank you

165
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:09,043
Is that good?

166
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:19,804
Why do humans drink this?

167
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:23,391
It's the same as you drinking blood, I guess

168
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:28,979
Aha

169
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,153
What is this?

170
00:11:37,321 --> 00:11:39,240
Is there a problem, sir?

171
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,743
This freaking coffee is neither hot nor cold
Is this a joke?

172
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:45,246
I'm sorry, I'll make you a fresh one

173
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,497
Forget it

174
00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:47,873
Just give me a refund

175
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:52,169
And I asked for whipped cream,
but there's no whipped cream here

176
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,088
Just a moment

177
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:57,550
Sir

178
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:00,803
You didn't actually order extra whipped cream

179
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:01,762
Hey

180
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,516
Do you think I'm lying?

181
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:08,978
Kids these days have bad manners

182
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,897
I'm sorry, I'll tell the boss

183
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:13,607
Are you a freaking idiot?

184
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:15,860
If the coffee's bad, we can make more

185
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:21,365
But it's hard to fix bad manners
